ransmitting station|Sudbury]]\n* [[Sutton Coldfield transmitting station|Sutton Coldfield]] ({{Coord|52|36|2|N|1|50|2|W|type:landmark_region:GB-BIR}})\n* [[Swingate transmitting station|Swingate]]\n* [[Tacolneston transmitting station|Tacolneston]]\n* [[Tapton Hill transmitting station|Tapton Hill/Sheffield (Crosspool)]]\n* [[Thrumster transmitting station|Thrumster]] ({{coord|58|23|38|N|3|7|28|W|type:landmark_region:GB}})\n* [[Torosay transmitting station|Torosay]] ({{coord|56|27|30|N|5|43|46|W|type:landmark_region:GB}})\n* [[Waltham transmitting station|Waltham]]\n* [[Washford transmitting station|Washford]] ({{coord|51|9|41|N|3|20|53|W|type:landmark_region:GB}})\n* [[Wenvoe transmitting station|Wenvoe]]\n* [[Westerglen transmitting station|Westerglen]]\n* [[West Kirby transmitting station|West Kirby]]\n* [[Winter Hill transmitting station|Winter Hill]] ({{coord|53|37|32|N|2|30|51|W|type:landmark_region:GB}})\n* [[The Wrekin transmitting station|The Wrekin]]\n* [[Wrotham transmitting station|Wrotham]]\n{{Col-end}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Digital One]] (A joint venture with [[GCap Media]] providing UK [[Digital audio broadcasting|DAB]] - wholly owned by Arqiva since 11 February 2008)\n* [[2RN (RT\u00c9 Networks)|2RN]] in [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]\n* [[Freeview (UK)|Freeview]]\n* [[VT Communications]] (Formerly Merlin Communications, formed from privatisation of [[BBC World Service]] transmitter sites.)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==Sources==\n* Pawley, Edward (1972). ''BBC Engineering 1922\u20131972''. London, BBC. {{ISBN|0-563-12127-0}}\n* Shacklady, Norman and Ellen, Martin (2003). ''On Air: A History of BBC Transmission''. Wavechange Books. {{ISBN|0-9544077-1-7}} (paperback) {{ISBN|0-9544077-0-9}} (hardback).\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|https://www.arqiva.com}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20101115094452/http://arqiva.com/broadcast/ Arqiva Online Virtual Tour]\n\n{{Telecommunications industry in the United Kingdom}}\n\n[[Category